body:
@sijie it probably shouldn't quietly fail with an Error 500 though.

Also, it would be very beneficial to just display the message ID and other metatadata, the message content isn't that important.

Currently, there's just no metadata displayed even in the overview list, just queue sequential numbers which are quite useless.

@vzhikserg Thank you very much for reporting this issue.
I find that there are more such issues in our docs, @Anonymitaet could you please help check and fix them once for all? Thank you.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/47805623/72773049-d954ac80-3c40-11ea-985e-2ba8af828b00.png)

@nareshgbhat Okay. It should be easy to bump the protobuf 3.5.1 to 3.6.

You don't need to worry about protobuf 2.4.1. It is a customized protoc for generating Pulsar Api. The java API has already been generated. So you don't need protoc runtime for 2.4.1.

I can send out a pull request if you can help me verify if it works on the ARM64 systems that would be great.
